						               													<description>ACP164 Albedo Combat Patrol provides the rules for playing skirmishes with miniatures in the science fiction setting of Steve Gallacci&amp;rsquo;s Albedo comics.&amp;#10;ACP164 can be played with as few as 4 figures per side up to company sized engagements with 50+ figures and supporting vehicles and flyers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The following components are required to play ACP164. &amp;#10;&amp;#10;     The Activation Deck is used to control the sequence in which units activate during a turn. &amp;#10;     The Action Deck is used to resolve fire, melee, and morale. Typically, each player has their own Action Deck. &amp;#10;     Various Markers denote wounds, stun, out of ammunition and morale. &amp;#10;     Unit Data Cards inform players of the attributes of the figures within the units they control as well as the weapons with which those units are equipped. &amp;#10;     Model figures, terrain, etc. are used as playing pieces in this tabletop game. &amp;#10;     Six-sided order dice are used as part of the Double Random ActivationTM mechanism to control the sequence in which units activate.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
